Pre-Game Insights: Kenya is the clear favorite in betting odds, with a better recent form compared to Mozambique.
Kenya has won three games while losing only two in their last five T20Is, and they are coming off a 4-wicket win against Nigeria following a 14-run defeat against the same opponent.
Mozambique has lost three while winning only two games in their last five fixtures, and they defeated Rwanda by 5 wickets in the previous T20I encounter.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch seems to be bowling-friendly with an average of 125 runs in the last five T20s, and spinners have dominated here as compared to the pacers in the game.
Rainy conditions expected, which could impact match proceedings.
Others: The match is set to take place between Kenya (KEN) and Mozambique (MOZ) on October 19 at 4:20 PM (IST) at the Ruaraka Sports Club Ground in Nairobi.

The probable playing XI for Kenya includes IA Karim (wk), SR Bhudia, Pushkar Sharma, Rushabvardhan Patel (C), RR Patel, Neil Mugabe, Francis Muia Mutua, Gerard Muthui, DM Gondaria, L Ndandason, PK Langat, and the probable playing XI for Mozambique includes Agostinho Navicha (wk), Jose Joao, F Nhaduate (C), M Manjate, Filipe Cossa, Joao Huo, Vieira Tembo, Dario Macome, E Ibraimo Azine, A Augusto Laice, and Camate Bez Raposo.
